107
00:09:40,990 --> 00:09:41,630
Try it.

108
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:53,020
It's a little hot.

109
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,900
Let me guess.
This was you when you were little.

110
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:14,830
Did someone give this to you?

111
00:10:19,830 --> 00:10:20,990
My dad

112
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:24,870
secretly stuffed it into my luggage

113
00:10:27,230 --> 00:10:29,540
when I moved to your house.

114
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:33,710
Your dad drew you so beautifully.

115
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:36,780
He must love you very much.

116
00:10:40,350 --> 00:10:42,470
But what's this?

117
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:54,850
(Dear Xingruo,
you'll always be my dear daughter.)

118
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:01,750
(Dear Xingruo,)

119
00:11:01,990 --> 00:11:04,230
(you'll always be my dear daughter.)

120
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:00,940
Who are you?

121
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,300
Lu Xingyan.

122
00:12:10,470 --> 00:12:13,420
So you wanted
to burn this painting that day.

123
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:24,540
After all these years,

124
00:12:25,660 --> 00:12:28,110
this is the first time I hear you
talk about your dad.

125
00:12:32,230 --> 00:12:34,420
My relationship with my dad

126
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:36,300
is quite complicated.

127
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:39,140
That's why

128
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:42,780
I never want to mention him.

129
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:45,470
It's because whenever I think of him,

130
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:49,230
it makes me miserable.

131
00:12:57,110 --> 00:13:00,940
So what happened back then?

132
00:13:03,710 --> 00:13:05,060
Can you tell me about it?

133
00:13:07,660 --> 00:13:09,590
When I was little,

134
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:15,630
my family was happy.

135
00:13:18,710 --> 00:13:19,510
My dad

136
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:22,470
is a famous artist,

137
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:25,590
so we're quite well-off.

138
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:29,420
My mom

139
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:31,940
is a famous pianist.

140
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:33,540
But she never played the piano again

141
00:13:34,110 --> 00:13:36,060
after getting married.

142
00:13:36,830 --> 00:13:37,780
I'm done.

143
00:13:38,830 --> 00:13:40,510
Here, let me see.

144
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:46,940
Am I not very good at drawing?

145
00:13:47,230 --> 00:13:47,990
Of course not.

146
00:13:47,990 --> 00:13:50,350
You did such a great job
that you surprised me.

147
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:51,110
I don't believe you.

148
00:13:51,110 --> 00:13:52,330
If you don't believe me,
show it to your mom.

149
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,300
Look.

150
00:13:56,020 --> 00:13:57,750
Baby, don't come over.
My hands are dirty.

151
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:58,830
You don't need to do the chores.

152
00:13:58,830 --> 00:13:59,870
We can just hire cleaners.

153
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:01,780
Cleaners won't clean
as seriously as yourself.

154
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:03,390
I clean the house thoroughly

155
00:14:03,390 --> 00:14:05,020
so that you feel comfortable.

156
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:06,230
Go play with your dad. Hurry.

157
00:14:06,590 --> 00:14:07,230
Ignore your mom.

158
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:08,510
She doesn't know anything.

159
00:14:08,990 --> 00:14:10,710
Let me explain.

160
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:11,780
Sit.

161
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:16,420
What you drew

162
00:14:16,470 --> 00:14:17,940
is called Cubism.

163
00:14:19,590 --> 00:14:21,300
This is a painting by Picasso.

164
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:23,020
Don't you think your drawings
are exactly the same?

165
00:14:23,020 --> 00:14:23,990
You're amazing.

166
00:14:23,990 --> 00:14:25,230
(I thought)

167
00:14:25,630 --> 00:14:28,230
(our family
could live happily like this forever.)

168
00:14:28,870 --> 00:14:30,780
(But I didn't expect)

169
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:32,750
(that there were cracks)

170
00:14:33,060 --> 00:14:34,660
(in my parents' relationship)

171
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:36,710
(that I couldn't see.)

172
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:37,940
Shen Guangyao.

173
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:40,230
How could you say that to me?

174
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:42,230
I quit my job

175
00:14:42,350 --> 00:14:44,020
and became what I am today.

176
00:14:44,540 --> 00:14:46,660
I did everything
for you and this family.

177
00:14:47,780 --> 00:14:49,110
I never deny

178
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:51,020
what you have done for this family.

179
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:53,390
But how come

180
00:14:53,390 --> 00:14:55,230
you keep finding fault with me?

181
00:14:55,230 --> 00:14:57,510
Either this is wrong or that is wrong!

182
00:14:58,230 --> 00:15:00,540
Where's the person who used to sit

183
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:01,420
at the piano?

184
00:15:02,260 --> 00:15:03,750
How did you become
someone who only cares

185
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:05,420
about the daily necessities of life?

186
00:15:05,420 --> 00:15:06,470
What do you want?

187
00:15:06,830 --> 00:15:07,900
Daily necessities of life?

188
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,000
Are you telling me
about daily necessities of life?

189
00:15:10,230 --> 00:15:11,750
Okay, let me ask you.

190
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,140
Someone has to buy the food in this house.

191
00:15:14,230 --> 00:15:16,230
Someone has to cook the daily meals.

192
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:17,710
You know Xingruo only likes to eat

193
00:15:17,710 --> 00:15:19,020
the food I cook.

194
00:15:19,590 --> 00:15:20,750
Aren't I

195
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:21,830
the only one

196
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:23,350
who's taking care of this family?

197
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:24,060
Enough!

198
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:26,180
Guangyao.

199
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:30,510
Stop living in your own world.

200
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:32,750
We need to take care of the family

201
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:33,780
together.

202
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:35,470
Can you understand me?

203
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:40,660
Dad and Mom.

204
00:15:41,370 --> 00:15:42,540
What's going on with you two?

205
00:15:43,630 --> 00:15:44,660
Nothing. Do your homework.

206
00:15:44,660 --> 00:15:45,710
- I'm talking to your mom.
- Nothing.

207
00:15:46,050 --> 00:15:47,020
Nothing, Xingruo.

208
00:15:47,510 --> 00:15:48,350
Nothing.

209
00:15:49,420 --> 00:15:51,060
Nothing, baby. Nothing.

210
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:53,020
Here, do your homework first.

211
00:15:53,990 --> 00:15:54,780
You must be hungry.

212
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:55,780
I'll make you

213
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:58,110
your favorite hot pot later, okay?

214
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:00,230
Here, go upstairs.

215
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:01,660
I'll call you when I'm done.

216
00:16:21,660 --> 00:16:23,230
After my mom died,

217
00:16:24,470 --> 00:16:26,660
I felt like the sky was falling.

218
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,350
I'm sorry for your loss.

219
00:16:36,450 --> 00:16:37,110
My condolences.

220
00:16:42,590 --> 00:16:44,590
(But to my dad,)

221
00:16:45,990 --> 00:16:48,180
(it was a relief.)

222
00:16:50,710 --> 00:16:52,710
(What I couldn't accept the most)

223
00:16:53,590 --> 00:16:54,900
(was that my dad)

224
00:16:55,830 --> 00:16:57,870
(got together with my head teacher,)

225
00:16:57,870 --> 00:16:58,990
(Ms. Fang.)

226
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:16,460
(You know what happened later.)

227
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:18,460
(I went to Mingli.)

228
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:20,790
(Then I went to university.)

229
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:23,630
(My dad
tried to contact me a few times,)

230
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:25,870
(but I never met him.)

231
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:28,350
(I never reply)

232
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:29,940
(to the text messages
he sent me either.)

233
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,180
Hello, welcome.

234
00:17:41,660 --> 00:17:42,740
Why are you here?

235
00:17:43,420 --> 00:17:44,870
I have an art exhibition here.

236
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:46,270
So I stopped by to see you.

237
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:52,270
Let me buy you coffee.

238
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:13,310
Why didn't you use
the money I gave you?

239
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:16,390
I think I'm doing pretty good.

240
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:17,740
I make my own living.

241
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:19,740
Didn't I say

242
00:18:20,110 --> 00:18:21,180
I don't need you?

243
00:18:24,350 --> 00:18:25,830
Why don't you understand it yet?

244
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,630
The fact that you are my daughter

245
00:18:28,630 --> 00:18:30,140
can never be changed.

246
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:33,630
Many years have passed.

247
00:18:34,830 --> 00:18:36,980
Shouldn't I move on?

248
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:39,270
Shouldn't I have my own life?

249
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:42,660
I beg you. Don't hate me.

250
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:44,350
You haven't changed

251
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:47,070
in all these years.

252
00:18:49,140 --> 00:18:51,390
You're lenient with yourself
and strict with others.

253
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:55,070
You have the right to choose your life.

254
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:56,030
I have the right

255
00:18:56,030 --> 00:18:57,870
to choose my life too.

256
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,550
I hope you don't exist in my life.

257
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:00,590
Please don't bother me anymore.

258
00:19:00,590 --> 00:19:01,660
Do you get what I mean?

259
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:10,790
If I knew

260
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:13,790
that was the last time
I would see him,

261
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:18,070
I wouldn't have been so harsh.

262
00:19:19,940 --> 00:19:22,110
I think my dad probably hates me.

263
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:25,180
Why do you say so?

264
00:19:28,460 --> 00:19:30,350
If he didn't hate me,

265
00:19:31,590 --> 00:19:32,790
why didn't he tell me

266
00:19:32,790 --> 00:19:34,180
he was sick?

267
00:19:35,790 --> 00:19:38,740
Why didn't he let me see him one last time?

268
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:42,630
No matter

269
00:19:42,630 --> 00:19:44,350
what the relationship between us
was like,

270
00:19:44,460 --> 00:19:46,270
I felt guilty

271
00:19:48,940 --> 00:19:50,790
for not saying goodbye to him properly.

272
00:19:53,310 --> 00:19:54,590
It's my regret.

273
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:07,900
Mr. Shen

274
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:12,420
might not be a good husband

275
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:16,550
or a good father,

276
00:20:19,420 --> 00:20:20,460
but I think

277
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,700
you don't have to hate him that much.

278
00:20:26,220 --> 00:20:27,940
